Thereupon he bade Mercury produce Psyche in heaven3 and holding out to her his ambrosial cup, “Take it‚” he said, “ and live forever 3 nor shall Cu- pid ever depart from theeff’ And the gods sat down together to the marriage-feast. On the first couch lay the bridegroom, and Psyche in his bosom. His rustic serving-boy bare the wine to Jupiter3 and Bac- chus to the rest, The Seasons crimsoned all things with their roses. Apollo sang to the lyre, while a little Pan prattled on his reeds, and Venus danced very sweetly to the soft music.
